						               													<description>Game description from the publisher:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Created by a backgammon champion, Mindgammon captures the essence of the original &amp;quot;backgammon&amp;quot;, but it's different.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game description by a BG Geek:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Mindgammon is most closely related to the Backgammon variant Acey-Duecy, where all 15 men start off the board and must be entered into the first 6 points (playing spaces) before the game can progress further.  Also a roll of 1-2, once played, is followed by a second move for that player.  Mindgammon has also taken elements of Old English Backgammon in that you are limited to 6 men per point.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The classic board is now laid out in a single column, making the game visually easier for beginners.  Bearing-off is by exact count only.  Also there are penalties for &amp;quot;unsportsmanlike&amp;quot; rolling of the dice, either out-of-turn or out-of-bounds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
